SIMPLE: particularize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Particularize
<hw>Par*tic"u*lar*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Particularized</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Particularizing</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>particulariser</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To give as a particular, or as the particulars; to mention
particularly; to give the particulars of; to enumerate or specify in
detail.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>particularise</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He not only boasts of his parentage as an Israelite, but
<qex>particularizes</qex> his descent from Benjamin.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Particularize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Particularize
<hw>Par*tic"u*lar*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To mention or attend
to particulars; to give minute details; to be circumstantial; <as>as, to
<ex>particularize</ex> in a narrative</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Particularly</ent>⟦br⟧
